Date: 27/1/1934
Source: Press, The
Author:
Vol / Page: 15
Edition:
Quote: Open shed.-S. where the shearers are not engaged beforehand, but roll up on the advertised day and take their chance of employment. I think the custom has quite gone out of use now. Anama in the late 'nineties was the last station I can remember to have seen advertising its starting day.
Notes:

